column12: Measurement condition : Clear; Partly Cloudy , No Precipitation , Heavy Wind
column13: No signs of major scour depsite large flood; some deposition D/S but not impacting model at this GH
column14: Too deep to wade; ARCBoat Lite @ gauge. Edge difficulty, esp on far bank.  @ Uncertainty: QRev Uncertainty Analysis (DS Mueller, 2016), 2-sigma value (1 x Uncertainty Value reported in *.xml File). @ Orifice line likely buried/fouled, causing painting, purged twice. 1740 logged reading was much lower; assume debris/sediment was removed by purge . Let sensor settle out during mmt, reset after. Used DWLs for MGH. Entire GH needs a full clean out and replacemment of wiring, Sunsaver is rusted from the flood, Remove all redundant sensors (shaft encoder? Accubar/N2 system). GH needs all new documentation & a new binder. Consider replacing shelter as this one is very likely going to be mouldy, and the well doesn't work anymore. Water was nearly 5 feet above gauge house floor in June!!!!!  ADCP by Moving Boat

Tied in hgih water mark. ADCP by Moving Boat
